## Context: JavaFX iChat Application Development with System Tray Integration

### 1. Previous Conversation:
The user requested development of a JavaFX iChat assistant application that evolved through multiple phases: initial code refactoring for better organization, fixing compilation errors, and finally implementing system tray integration. The conversation began with the user asking to "refactor code properly" while keeping all functionality intact. The original codebase consisted of a floating button application with drag functionality and a chat sidebar interface. After successful refactoring into a modular architecture with proper package structure, the user requested the button behave like system dock icons (similar to IntelliJ and other applications), leading to the current work on implementing proper system tray integration.

